NASA yesterday held a closed-door meeting with the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission amid tension over electronic transmission demands.&ldquo;NASA are our clients and they came for a normal consultation,&rdquo; said IEBC communications manager Andrew Limo. The IEBC said the teams discussed voter verification, nominations, campaigns, voting and the elections conference.NASA last Sunday dragged three local mobile phone service providers into fresh demands to the IEBC to ensure tallying is successful. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s the responsibility of the commission to ensure achievement of this legal requirement without any alterations whatsoever,&rdquo; warned NASA campaign chairman Musalia Mudavadi in a statement on Sunday. The pentagon wants Safaricom, Airtel and Telkom to provide encrypted Sim cards that will protect their transmission systems from hacking.